<paragraph pageId="156" pageNumber="157">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="156" pageNumber="157">English</emphasis>
: catbrier, greenbrier.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="156" pageNumber="157" type="range">
<paragraph pageId="156" pageNumber="157">Range.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="156" pageNumber="157">Southern Europe to Asia in the Himalayas. In Myanmar, found in Chin, Kachin, and Shan.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="156" pageNumber="157" type="uses">
<paragraph pageId="156" pageNumber="157">Uses.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="156" pageNumber="157">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="156" pageNumber="157">Root</emphasis>
: Used as an emetic and diaphoretic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
